description:
On May 7, 2021, Colonial Pipeline, the largest fuel pipeline operator in the United States, was hit by ransomware. For an entire week, the East Coast was paralyzed: fuel shortages, flights rerouted, and panic buying that echoed the oil crises of the 1970s. But this incident revealed a darker truth: America’s critical infrastructure was vulnerable and unprotected.
